## MUI Usage Rules

### Forms & Inputs
- Always use `MUI TextField` with `variant="outlined"` and `size="small"`.
- Group related fields using `MUI Grid` (`container` + `item`) — never stack them manually.
- Required fields must show the asterisk via `required` prop — do not add `*` in the label string.
- Use `MUI Select` for dropdowns with 3 or more options. For 2 or fewer, use `RadioGroup`.
- Date inputs must use `MUI DatePicker` from `@mui/x-date-pickers`.
- Form validation errors appear as `helperText` on the field — never as alert banners for field-level errors.
- Every form must have a primary `Submit` button and a `Cancel` button. Never use only one button.

### Buttons
- Primary action: `variant="contained"` with `color="primary"` (green).
- Secondary/cancel: `variant="outlined"`.
- Destructive action (delete, mark lost): `variant="contained"` with `color="error"`.
- Icon-only buttons must always include a `tooltip` (MUI `Tooltip` wrapper).
- Maximum **one** primary button per card or form section.

### Modals / Dialogs
- Use `MUI Dialog` for all confirmations, quick-edit forms, and detail overlays.
- Destructive confirmation dialogs must always spell out what will be deleted/changed in the body text.
- Modal max widths: `xs` for confirmations, `sm` for simple forms, `md` for complex forms, `lg` for quote builder.
- Always trap focus inside open modals (MUI handles this by default — don't override).

### Data Tables
- Use `MUI DataGrid` for all list views (leads, contacts, projects, quotes).
- Always include: column sorting, pagination (page size options: 10, 25, 50), and a search/filter bar above the table.
- Row click opens the detail view — do not use a separate "View" button column.
- Action buttons (edit, delete) live in the final column using `renderCell`.
- Never show more than 8 columns by default. Hide secondary columns behind a column visibility toggle.

### Charts
- Use `MUI X Charts` or `Recharts` — do not mix both in the same project.
- All charts must have a `title` prop displayed above the chart in `h6` typography.
- Charts must handle empty/zero states gracefully — show a placeholder message, not a broken chart.
- Pie charts: maximum 6 slices. Combine smaller categories into "Other" beyond that.
- Bar charts: use horizontal bars when there are more than 5 categories.
- All chart colors must pull from the brand palette — never use default library colors.

### Stat / KPI Cards
- Each stat card shows: label, primary value, and an optional trend indicator (up/down arrow + % change).
- Cards render in a responsive row using `MUI Grid` — 4 columns on desktop, 2 on tablet, 1 on mobile.
- Use `lucide-react` icons in the top-right of each stat card. Icon size: `20px`.

