## Navigation & Layout

- Sidebar navigation — always visible on desktop, collapsible to icon-only on tablet, drawer on mobile.
- Sidebar order: Dashboard → Leads → Contacts → Projects → Quotes → Tasks → Reports → Settings.
- Active sidebar item uses `primary` green background with white text.
- Page header includes: page title (h5), breadcrumb trail, and a primary CTA button (e.g. "Add Lead").
- Breadcrumbs use `>` separator and link all levels except the current page.

---

## Empty States

Every list view and data table must handle the case where there is no data:
- Show a `lucide-react` icon relevant to the section (e.g. `UserCircle` for contacts).
- Show a short message: `"No [leads] yet"`.
- Show a primary CTA button: `"Add your first [lead]"`.
- Never show a blank white box.

---

## Responsive Breakpoints (MUI defaults)

| Breakpoint | Width | Layout Behavior |
|---|---|---|
| `xs` | 0–600px | Single column, mobile drawer nav |
| `sm` | 600–900px | Two columns, icon-only sidebar |
| `md` | 900–1200px | Full sidebar, 3-col grids |
| `lg` | 1200px+ | Full layout, 4-col stat cards |

Always test layouts at `sm` and `md` — these are the most common screen sizes for field reps on tablets.